f(x, y, z)\cdot\big(x(3y^2+3z^2+3yz+1) + y(3x^2+3z^2+3xz+1) + z(3x^2+3y^2+3xy+1)\big) \\ \geqslant (x+y+z)^2 = 1.
f(x, y, z) \geqslant \frac{1}{3(xy^2 + xz^2 + yx^2 + yz^2 + zx^2 + zy^2 + 3xyz) + x+y+z} \\ =\frac{1}{3(x+y+z)(xy+yz+xz) + 1} = \frac{1}{3(xy+yz+xz) + 1}
xy + yz + xz
